    • loadScene

      public javafx.scene.Scene loadScene(String filepath, boolean cacheLastUsedScene, boolean useCachedScene) throws IOException

      loadScene is used to create a Scene using a fxml document of the users choosing. the fxml document has to be inside the resources file in a JavaFX project.

      if the user wants to use a cached Scene, the Scene that bears the same filepath as the one the user wants will be returned, unless there is no Scene that is stored in the cache with the same filepath, in which case a new Scene will be loaded with the desired fxml document.

      if the user does not want to use a cached Scene, all Scenes that use the same filepath will be deleted from cache and a new Scene will be loaded with the desired fxml document

      if the user chooses not to save the old Scene in cache, the old Scene will be removed from cache

      additionally, the function initially checks if the fxml file resides within a directory that has the same name as the class, meaning that the user can search for the fxml directly (example: "group/projectname/view.fmxl" can be searched with "view")

      User needs to open the directory the .fxml file resides in to the library within module-info.java

      Parameter:
      filepath - defines which fxml document should be loaded
      cacheLastUsedScene - defines if the previous Scene should be cached or not
      useCachedScene - defines if the current Scene should be fetched from the cache or not
      Gibt zurück:
      returns the wanted Scene
      Löst aus:
      IOException - throws an error if the wanted fxml document cannot be found
